data.enText: bad-tempered or not speaking because you are angry about sth

data.chText: 萨拉一上午都不高兴地板着脸。
data.enText: Sarah had looked sulky all morning.

tr: a light two-wheeled vehicle for one person

example: the glooming interior of an old inn

value.def: Someone who is sulky is sulking or is unwilling to enjoy themselves.

example.ex: I was quite sulky, so I didn't take part in much.
example.tran: 我很烦，所以没有积极参与。

value.tran: 面有愠色的;生闷气的;闷闷不乐的

example.ex: 'You haven't got the right attitude,' he said sulkily.
example.tran: 他怄气道：“你态度不端正。”
